TITLE: Installing NVM and Node.js
DESCRIPTION: These bash commands install Node Version Manager (NVM) and a recommended version of Node.js. NVM allows managing multiple Node.js versions. The `corepack enable` command enables Yarn package manager which is required to install dependencies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/local-setup.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
sudo apt-get install curl

curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/master/install.sh | bash

nvm install # installs recommended node version

nvm use # use recommended node version

corepack enable
```

