TITLE: Descriptive Variable Naming in React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet contrasts bad and good variable naming practices within a React component using `useState`. The 'bad' example uses a generic variable name, while the 'good' example employs a descriptive name that clearly indicates the variable's purpose.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/best-practices-front.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
