TITLE: Using useRecoilState for State Management in React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use `useRecoilState` to manage state in a React component with Recoil. It defines an atom `myAtomState` with a default value and then uses `useRecoilState` to bind the atom to a component's state, allowing the component to read and update the state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/best-practices-front.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
export const myAtomState = atom({
  key: 'myAtomState',
  default: 'default value',
});

export const MyComponent = () => {
  const [myAtom, setMyAtom] = useRecoilState(myAtomState);

  return (
    <div>
      <input
        value={myAtom}
        onChange={(e) => setMyAtom(e.target.value)}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

