TITLE: Zod Schema Validation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code shows an example of using Zod for schema validation in JavaScript. It defines a schema for an object with boolean, email and password properties and sets the properties to required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/best-practices-front.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
const validationSchema = z
  .object({
    exist: z.boolean(),
    email: z
      .string()
      .email('Email must be a valid email'),
    password: z
      .string()
      .regex(PASSWORD_REGEX, 'Password must contain at least 8 characters'),
  })
  .required();

type Form = z.infer<typeof validationSchema>;
```

