TITLE: Listening for Hotkeys in a Modal Component (Escape Key) - TSX
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to listen for the Escape key in a modal component using the `useScopedHotkeys` hook. It utilizes the `onClose` prop to trigger a function when the Escape key is pressed, effectively closing the modal.  It relies on `Key.Escape`, `onClose` and `ExampleHotkeyScopes.ExampleModal`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/hotkeys.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const MyDropdownComponent = ({ onClose }: { onClose: () => void }) => {
  // 2. Use the useScopedHotkeys hook to listen for Escape.
  // Note that escape is a common hotkey that could be used by many other components
  // So it's important to use a hotkey scope to avoid conflicts
  useScopedHotkeys(
    Key.Escape,
    () => {
      onClose()
    },
    ExampleHotkeyScopes.ExampleModal,
  );

  return <div>My modal component</div>;
};
```

