TITLE: Using AppTooltip Component in React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the `AppTooltip` component to display additional information on hover.  It imports the `AppTooltip` component from the specified path and defines a React component that renders a paragraph and an `AppTooltip` associated with it. It showcases how to set properties like content, delayHide, offset, and placement of the tooltip. The anchorSelect prop links the tooltip to the paragraph element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/twenty-ui/display/app-tooltip.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { AppTooltip } from "@/ui/display/tooltip/AppTooltip";

export const MyComponent = () => {
  return (
    <>
      <p id="hoverText" style={{ display: "inline-block" }}>
        Customer Insights
      </p>
      <AppTooltip
        className
        anchorSelect="#hoverText"
        content="Explore customer behavior and preferences"
        delayHide={0}
        offset={6}
        noArrow={false}
        isOpen={true}
        place="bottom"
        positionStrategy="absolute"
      />
    </>
  );
};
```

