TITLE: Using MenuItemSelect in React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the MenuItemSelect component with an icon, text, and selection state. It also includes an onClick handler function that logs a message to the console when the menu item is selected. The component imports IconBell from "@tabler/icons-react" and MenuItemSelect from "twenty-ui/display".
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/twenty-ui/navigation/menu-item.mdx#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { IconBell } from "@tabler/icons-react";
import { MenuItemSelect } from "twenty-ui/display";

export const MyComponent = () => {
  const handleSelection = () => {
    console.log("Menu item selected");
  };

  return (
    <MenuItemSelect
      LeftIcon={IconBell}
      text="First Option"
      selected={true}
      disabled={false}
      hovered={false}
      onClick={handleSelection}
      className
    />
  );
};
```

