TITLE: Message Queue Worker Example in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a worker class that processes messages from a specific queue. It includes dependency injection using `@Inject` to obtain an instance of `MessageQueueService` and defines an `initWorker` method that sets up the worker to process incoming messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/backend-development/queue.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
//async worker
class CustomWorker {
  constructor(@Inject(MESSAGE_QUEUES.custom) private queue: MessageQueueService) {
    this.initWorker();
  }

  async initWorker() {
    await this.queue.work(async ({ id, data }) => {
      //worker logic
    });
  }
}
```

