TITLE: Toggle Component Usage React
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the Toggle component from the twenty-ui library in a React application. It showcases setting the initial value, handling the onChange event, and customizing the color and size. The value prop sets the current state of the toggle (true or false), onChange is a callback function triggered when the toggle state changes, color customizes the appearance when it's 'on', and toggleSize adjusts the visual dimensions.
