TITLE: React FC - Good Example TSX
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates defining a separate type (OwnProps) for component props, avoiding the automatic inclusion of the `children` prop provided by `React.FC`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/style-guide.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
/* ✅ - Good, a separate type (OwnProps) is explicitly defined for the 
 *      component's props
 *    - This method doesn't automatically include the children prop. If
 *      you want to include it, you have to specify it in OwnProps.
 */ 
type EmailFieldProps = {
  value: string;
};

const EmailField = ({ value }: EmailFieldProps) => (
  <TextInput value={value} disabled fullWidth />
);
```

