TITLE: Imports Alias Usage
DESCRIPTION: This snippet contrasts bad and good importing practices by utilizing designated aliases. The 'bad' example uses relative path, while the 'good' example employs the alias.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/best-practices-front.mdx#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
// ❌ Bad, specifies the entire relative path
import {
  CatalogDecorator
} from '../../../../../testing/decorators/CatalogDecorator';
import {
  ComponentDecorator
} from '../../../../../testing/decorators/ComponentDecorator';
```

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
// ✅ Good, utilises the designated aliases
import { CatalogDecorator } from '~/testing/decorators/CatalogDecorator';
import { ComponentDecorator } from 'twenty-ui/testing';
```

