TITLE: Restoring Database to New Postgres:16 Container
DESCRIPTION: These commands restore the database to the new postgres:16 container using `psql`. It first copies the dump file to the container, enters the container's shell, and then executes the `psql` command to restore the database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/self-hosting/upgrade-guide.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
docker cp databases_backup.sql twenty-db-1:/databases_backup.sql
docker exec -it twenty-db-1 sh
psql -U {YOUR_POSTGRES_USER} -d {YOUR_POSTGRES_DB} -f databases_backup.sql
exit
```

