TITLE: FloatingIconButtonGroup Usage Example in React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet showcases the usage of the FloatingIconButtonGroup component. It uses an array of objects to define icon buttons with properties for Icon, onClick, and isActive. It uses size and className props for the group. Imports FloatingIconButtonGroup from '@/ui/input/button/components/' and icons from '@tabler/icons-react'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/twenty-ui/input/buttons.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { FloatingIconButtonGroup } from "@/ui/input/button/components/FloatingIconButtonGroup";
import { IconClipboardText, IconCheckbox } from "@tabler/icons-react";

export const MyComponent = () => {
  const iconButtons = [
    {
      Icon: IconClipboardText,
      onClick: () => console.log("Button 1 clicked"),
      isActive: true,
    },
    {
      Icon: IconCheckbox,
      onClick: () => console.log("Button 2 clicked"),
      isActive: true,
    },
  ];

  return (
    <FloatingIconButtonGroup 
    className 
    size="small" 
    iconButtons={iconButtons} />
  );
};
```

