TITLE: Creating Kubernetes Server Secret
DESCRIPTION: This command creates a Kubernetes secret named `tokens` within the `twentycrm` namespace. The secret stores access, login, refresh, and file tokens as literal values.  It is crucial to replace `changeme` with secure, randomly generated values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-docker/k8s/README.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
kubectl create secret generic -n twentycrm tokens --from-literal accessToken=changeme --from-literal loginToken="changeme" --from-literal refreshToken="changeme" --from-literal fileToken="changeme"
```

