TITLE: Defining TrackEventProperties Type
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a generic type `TrackEventProperties<T>` that maps event names to their corresponding properties types using the `TrackEvents` interface.  If the event name `T` exists as a key in `TrackEvents`, it extracts the 'properties' type from the corresponding event type in `TrackEvents`. Otherwise, it defaults to an empty object type. This ensures type safety when accessing event properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-server/src/engine/core-modules/analytics/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Define the mapping between event names and their event types
export interface TrackEvents {
  [EVENT_NAME_1]: Event1Type;
  [EVENT_NAME_2]: Event2Type;
  // ... other event types
}

// Use the mapping to extract properties for each event type
export type TrackEventProperties<T extends TrackEventName> = T extends keyof TrackEvents
  ? TrackEvents[T]['properties']
  : object;
```

