TITLE: Avoiding Default Values for Optional Props in React
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the best practice of avoiding passing default values for optional props in React components. It shows that explicitly passing a value that is the same as the default value is redundant and unnecessary.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/blob/main/packages/twenty-website/src/content/developers/frontend-development/best-practices-front.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
type EmailFieldProps = {
  value: string;
  disabled?: boolean;
};

const EmailField = ({ value, disabled = false }: EmailFieldProps) => (
  <TextInput value={value} disabled={disabled} fullWidth />
);
```

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
// ❌ Bad, passing in the same value as the default value adds no value
const Form = () => <EmailField value="username@email.com" disabled={false} />;
```

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
// ✅ Good, assumes the default value
const Form = () => <EmailField value="username@email.com" />;
```

